    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix memory leak in job list removal function\n\n### Summary\nThe `remove_job()` function in the OMG module had a logic issue that caused improper list traversal when removing jobs. Specifically, the redundant condition check `if (current == list || previous == NULL)` could lead to incorrect behavior when trying to remove jobs from the job list.\n\nThis manifested as jobs not being properly removed from the list in certain scenarios, causing the job list to grow indefinitely and leading to memory exhaustion over time. The issue was particularly noticeable in long-running simulations with frequent node additions and removals.\n\nThe fix simplifies the head-of-list check to use only `previous == NULL`, which is sufficient and clearer. This ensures proper list traversal and job removal behavior.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/UTIL/OMG/job.c`: Simplified the condition in `remove_job()` function from `if (current == list || previous == NULL)` to `if (previous == NULL)` for cleaner logic when removing the first element of the job list.\n"
}